reviews.text:
Too SALTY! I had Sunday lunch with a friend at Happy Time Saloon in mid February 2019. We ordered the handmade purple cabbage dumplings & pork curry. The curry was over-cooked, the dumplings were fresh and good but the meals were both so salty I couldn’t enjoy them. It was $120 for the two small meals and we were both hungry after because they were too small. overpriced and disappointing. 
The service was friendly and dogs are welcome to sit with their humans in the alfresco outdoor seating.
Very good taste for special taste people
Nice food(vegetarian food is also available) with clean environment. The boss is very friendly and she loves cats and dogs. Highly recommend this restaurant to everyone who visits Kamtin!!
